+## Syntax-Preflight Implementation Constraints
+
+The daemon syntax-preflight repair must be narrow and deterministic:
+
+- Change `ppd/daemon/ppd_daemon.py` only, unless a focused daemon test is explicitly required by the active task.
+- Add a helper that derives changed Python files from `proposal.changed_files` and checks each with `python3 -m py_compile `.
+- Add a helper that derives changed TypeScript files from `proposal.changed_files` and checks them with the existing strict `npx tsc --noEmit --target ES2020 --module ESNext --moduleResolution node --strict --skipLibCheck --types node ` command.
+- Run syntax-preflight after file replacement and before full validation.
+- If syntax-preflight fails, restore all backed-up files immediately, set `failure_kind` to `syntax_preflight`, persist the failed patch, and skip full validation for that proposal.
+- If no changed `.py`, `.ts`, or `.tsx` files exist, syntax-preflight must run no commands and full validation may proceed normally.
+- Do not implement or retry `ppd/contracts/planned_crawl_manifest.py` while repairing syntax-preflight.
 
